<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[801,1453,1218,1466]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis box="[839,896,1218,1241]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Notes</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[930,1153,1218,1242]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Lejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis box="[930,1153,1218,1242]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Lejeunea rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a robust Andean species with orbicular leaves, very large and suborbicular underleaves with a short-bifid apex and strongly auriculate bases, and stems with 4–6 cell wide ventral merophytes (
<bibRefCitation author="REINER-DREHWALD, M. E." pageId="5" pageNumber="46" pagination="687 - 692" refId="ref8882" refString="REINER-DREHWALD, M. E. (2005). On Lejeunea rotundifolia and Dicladolejeunea (Lejeuneaceae, Jungermanniopsida). Syst. Bot. 30: 687 - 692." type="journal article" year="2005">REINER-DREHWALD, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[872,1106,1346,1370]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Taxilejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="auriculata">
<emphasis box="[872,1106,1346,1370]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Taxilejeunea auriculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identical to 
<taxonomicName box="[1259,1406,1346,1370]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Lejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis box="[1259,1406,1346,1370]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">L. rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a synonym. The specimen collected by Allioni is chosen here as the 
<typeStatus box="[842,938,1410,1434]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[972,1100,1410,1434]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Taxilejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="auriculata">
<emphasis box="[972,1100,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">T. auriculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it was illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="STEPHANI, F." pageId="5" pageNumber="46" refId="ref9306" refString="STEPHANI, F. (1985). Icones Hepaticarum. Microfiche edition. IDC, Zug." type="book" year="1985">STEPHANI (1985</bibRefCitation>
: tab. 9997).
</paragraph>
